<DOC><DOCNO> AP900131-0147 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-31-90 1644EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-People-Jackson     01-31 0134</FIRST><SECOND>AM-People-Jackson,0139</SECOND><HEAD>Maynard Jackson III Pleads No Contest to Marijuana Possesion</HEAD><DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Maynard Jackson III, the son of Atlanta's mayor,was fined the maximum $150 after he pleaded no contest to amisdemeanor charge of marijuana possession.   The action came Tuesday in Atlanta Traffic Court.   The younger Jackson also was found guilty of a charge offollowing too closely, and Judge Andrew Hairston fined him $60 onthat charge.   The judge ordered Jackson to report back to court in 30 days topay the fines.   Jackson was charged after a Jan. 9 traffic accident in Atlanta'sBuckhead neighborhood, a day before his 19th birthday. Police saidthey found several marijuana cigarettes in his car.   Mayor Maynard Jackson had said he wanted his son to receive nospecial treatment by city authorities.</TEXT></DOC>